'''[[casus]] [[foederis]]''' [[w:casus foederis]] is a diplomatic term with implications regarding whether it is appropriate to go to war.  i.e. Resolve political disputes and conflicting interests by state organized resort to arms.  The concept played a key role in the rapid escalation to global conflict in the first world war.

An example of usage from the alleged secret treaty allying Turkey and Germany in the first world war [[http://www.lib.byu.edu/~rdh/wwi/1914/germturk.html]]: "2. In case Russia should intervene with active military measures, and should thus bring about a casus foederis for Germany with relation to Austria-Hungary, this casus foederis would also come into existence for Turkey."

